Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032

Preamble: My TERT Mission 4. The procedure for the award of cash prizes to the winning local bodies in the 12 categories of TERT Mission 4. 0 and the appropriation of this prize money has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27th September, 2024 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 26th August, 2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.

Government Decision: Considering the points mentioned in the Preamble, the total amount received by the Sillod Municipal Council under my AGENT Mission 4.0 is Rs. The proposal was submitted by the Sillod Municipal Council. constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.
Government Decision No: MAWA-0825 / P.No.159 (8) / T. A. 1.

The date of the committee was considered at its meetings held on 26 August 2025. As per the recommendation made by the said Committee, the total amount submitted by the Sillod Municipal Council is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing Rs. 47,86, 837.00 (Rupees Forty Seven Lakh ASM One Thousand Eight Hundred and Thirty-Second only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
1) The Sillod Municipal Council will be the operational mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) Expenditure in excess of the prize money should be made out of self-funding.

5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available 4. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been accorded administrative sanction by the Government as per paragraphs-9 and 2 above, the remaining amount of the prize money to the Sillod Municipal Council is Rs. The Government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹1 lakh (Rupees Twenty Five Lakhs only) through Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
